<subSubSection id="255686ED0A60A460EA21A561099A5EEF" pageId="33" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E0C1B3358BEBD428BD448493C12DB90D" pageId="33" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="226F2D671E0796B6AA173045E4D180E2" pageId="33" pageNumber="44">
Coxa widely separated, epipleural lobes strongly produced. 
<bibRefCitation id="5E8C8827B2DE96FD1ECA1DE252DBCCA1" author="Chamorro-Lacayo, ML" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="56" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 46" title="Morphology of the prothorax and procoxa in the New World Cryptocephalini (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cryptocephalinae)." volume="676" year="2004">Chamorro-Lacayo and Konstantinov (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, provided several prothoracic characters: pronotal punctures absent; intercoxal prosternal process truncate; anterior margin of intercoxal prosternal process with a medial flange, or two submedial flanges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4729B468B93A54E2A0B0D954FBDF71D6" pageId="33" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="094FF1454A70581F7F9C09FB690B4C83" pageId="33" pageNumber="44">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3CDEB650F3531FC4507DDA7DB9F6B34F" pageId="33" pageNumber="44">From Costa Rica to Argentina, mainly in tropical regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C028F933E1323F66883F448802FCA9EA" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F8566FC27BCA5AEACFEB016E351CA289" pageId="34" pageNumber="45">
<pageBreakToken id="2F8DAF68B54FF1F8EB1820A7F858DF89" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" start="start">Remarks</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09D74B0199682C13498F853B219CC63A" pageId="34" pageNumber="45">
<bibRefCitation id="49D7500FE43C164F9D41CB09AD28B3CB" author="Weise, J" journalOrPublisher="Arkiv fuer zoologi" pageId="64" pageNumber="75" pagination="11 - 205" title="Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der schwedischen Entomologischen Reise des Herrn Dr. A. Roman in Amazonas." volume="14" year="1921">Weise (1921)</bibRefCitation>
disagreed with the separation of this genus from 
<taxonomicName id="5E35C458AA7B03B20D7A54FA667C2555" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cryptocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cryptocephalus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cryptocephalus</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="F0E62776A6058E70B38B5F6DD2E926CA" author="White, RE" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C." pageId="64" pageNumber="75" title="A review of the genus Cryptocephalus in America north of Mexico (Chrysomelidae: Coleoptera)." year="1968">White (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, interpreted 
<normalizedToken id="7E4CDC6D0860FC29BD3775BFD88FD7F0" originalValue="Weise’s">Weise's</normalizedToken>
comment as the synonymyzation of 
<taxonomicName id="D073BF2D0A000BD49D53190B81D75919" authority="Baly, 1877" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stegnocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stegnocephala" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Stegnocephala</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="6A1DAA71D37812A3904E0727C92803F5" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cryptocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cryptocephalus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cryptocephalus</taxonomicName>
. Since 
<bibRefCitation id="5180B884C36B9D7AC563EBC12DB6049A" author="Weise, J" journalOrPublisher="Arkiv fuer zoologi" pageId="64" pageNumber="75" pagination="11 - 205" title="Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der schwedischen Entomologischen Reise des Herrn Dr. A. Roman in Amazonas." volume="14" year="1921">Weise (1921)</bibRefCitation>
only provided morphological differences of 
<taxonomicName id="C47A2C816558F2BEC32B49973627F56C" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cryptocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cryptocephalus perplexus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexus">Cryptocephalus perplexus</taxonomicName>
Suffrian, which is not the type species of the genus, we still consider 
<taxonomicName id="7569D9CD0A9A466BDA148A2AC7E55542" authority="Baly, 1877" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stegnocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stegnocephala" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Stegnocephala</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus. Chamorro is currently revising the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="034BF8C0A09E7308332ABE6963C3253D" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" type="argentinian species checklist">
<paragraph id="EAEC5585F48A21782C125ECF5D4AC54F" pageId="34" pageNumber="45">Argentinian species checklist.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="51C218C109132FB8F1F5394B003A9673" pageId="34" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="80926AB14263D09F027A250E1B11C3EB" authority="Baly, 1877" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stegnocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stegnocephala discoidalis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discoidalis">Stegnocephala discoidalis</taxonomicName>
Baly, 1877c (MNS).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B862F5DFE0920987FCAF0768D7F783D" pageId="34" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="2EACA7D3EEFEF6CB7A6FC84CD47F2D94" authority="Baly, 1877" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stegnocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stegnocephala xanthopyga" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthopyga">Stegnocephala xanthopyga</taxonomicName>
(Suffrian, 1863) (TUC). This species newly cited for Argentina (Tucuman, 
<normalizedToken id="5F7FC9F9E52177B0BA659C07595E6710" originalValue="Famaillá">Famailla</normalizedToken>
: Quebrada de Lules, 30-I-1942 // F. 
<normalizedToken id="D6E43DF05F9FE37CF7DB0A81DC159CA2" originalValue="Monrós">Monros</normalizedToken>
Collection 1959).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
